title: For Sale:  US WWII 37mm Antitank Gun Breechring Registered DD
postcontent: The carriage is gone and the breechring is left and for sale. US M3 37mm Antitank Gun breechring and block, complete, plus accessories for sale. This is an NFA Registered Destructive Device. Marked on ring: Gun 37mm M3 NO. 23557 ORD. DEPT. U.S.A. U.S Machine Corp. 1943 191 LBS. INSP. B.O.L. This is a complete ring and block, ready to screw on and fire. This block was precision saw-cut – ‘demilled’ – in order to import it back in the 1980’s. See photos. The cut is 0.5” wide by 2” long. Even with this cut I chose to register the ring as a Destructive Device with the BATF in 2003; I could not verify with the BATF that even ‘demilled’ it would never be construed as a DD as it functions as designed, and theoretically could fire live rounds (at least one anyway). Absent BATF endorsement I decided it best to register. Therefore, transfer to the new owner will require an approved BATFE Form 4. As it sits it is fully functional as a blank-firing breechring. I have fired hundreds of rounds with it with no failures, issues or any danger whatsoever. However, in no way should the buyer assume this ring is safe for firing live projectile rounds. Terms of sale will include the buyer executing a separate agreement stating Buyer acknowledges the ring is not deemed safe for use with live projectile rounds and relieves Seller / Manufacturer from any and all liability. Also included in this sale as a package are as follows: 1. Faux Projectile Blank Adapter Complete 10 gauge (2) 2. Faux Projectile Adapter Insert 12 gauge (1) 3. Shotgun Blanks: 12 gauge (100) 4. Blackpowder Blanks: 10 gauge (100) 5. Bore brush, 37mm: 2 6. Bore swabs, 37mm: 2 7. Casings, 37mm w/ primer inserts (6) 8. Firing Pin, spare (2) The ‘Faux Projectile Blank Adapters’ are custom machined from an original 37mm shell casing with a faux projectile that screws into a tubular insert that accepts a 10 gauge or 12 gauge blank round. There are two complete units with 10 gauge inserts and one additional 12 gauge insert. There are six original 37mm cases used for handloading black powder blank rounds using the original cases. The original primers are pushed out and custom brass inserts pressed into the brass case 9no alteration to the case). The new inserts accept .50 BMG primers and therefore the rounds function like normal. I have reprimed, reloaded and fired each of these cases maybe 4-5 times each. The swabs and brushes are current production, non-military. I made my own cleaning rods and installed matching threaded inserts. You can have these rods if you want to pay postage or pick them up in person. Located near Houston, TX. Here are the photos: http://s214.photobucket.com/user/R_S_Hu ... breechring Terms: Buyer is responsible for submitting the BATFE Form 4, arranging shipping and all transfer fees. Buyer must sign and notarize ‘Not For use with live Projectile Rounds’ release document. Payment is due before the Form 4 is submitted. I am happy to ship everything but the ring upon receipt of payment. Physical pickup is fine too.
